headline: Auto tariffs, Berkshire earnings, Fed meeting: What to Watch
summary: To close out today's Market Domination Overtime, hosts Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton preview the biggest stories and earnings reports to come next week, including President Trump's tariff on auto tariffs which will take effect this Saturday; Berkshire Hathaway (BRK-B, BRK-A) announcing quarterly results at its annual shareholders meeting; Palantir (PLTR), Ford (FORD), and Disney (DIS) will also release earnings; and Federal Reserve' officials will be convening in Washington, D.C. for their May FOMC meeting. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.

headline: This Week In Electric Vehicles - Charging Market Soars with Tech Innovations and Policy Support
summary: The electric vehicle (EV) charging station market is set for substantial growth, driven by rising EV adoption, supportive government policies, and advances in charging technology. The global market, valued at USD 39.7 billion in 2024, is projected to reach USD 363.3 billion by 2034, with DC fast charging projected to exceed USD 180 billion due to increasing demand for long-distance EV travel capabilities. Government incentives and regulatory measures are crucial in expanding charging...
